The MTA claims that fare evasion has cost the city $260 million in revenue this year alone.
“[Fare evasion] is unfair to the vast majority of New Yorkers who pay the fare,” Donovan said.
In 2016, young Black men, ages 16 to 36 years old, represented half of all fare evasion arrests in Brooklyn, according to the CSS report.
Its goal, the NYPD said, is to ensure riders understand that fare evasion is illegal through their signage in every station.